The following assumptions were made regarding the financial plan:
&nbsp;
* Predicted sales of \$8,424
&nbsp;
* Predicted increase in the balance sheet (assets) accounts proportional to sales

Now, let us compute the percentage of cost in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Cost}&=\frac{\text{Cost}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$4,730}{\$7,200}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.66}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{66\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of cost in proportion to the sales is 66\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected cost:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Cost}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$8,424}\times{66\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$5,559.84}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected cost is \$5,559.84.**

Now, let us compute the projected net income:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Net Income}&=\text{Sales}-\text{Cost}\\[12pt]
&={\$8,424}-{\$5,559.84}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$2,864.16}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected net income is \$2,864.16.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of cost in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Asset}&=\frac{\text{Asset}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$21,700}{\$7,200}\times100\\[12pt]
&={3.01}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{301\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of asset in proportion to the sales is 301\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Assets}&=\text{Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$8,424}\times{301\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$25,356.24}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected assets is \$25,356.24.**

Now, let us compute the total debt and equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Debt and Equity}&=\text{Debt}+\text{Equity}\\[12pt]
&={\$9,100}+{\$12,600}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$21,700}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The total debt and equity amounts to \$21,700.**

Now, let us compute the total equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Equity}&=\text{Equity}+\text{Retained Earnigns}\\[12pt]
&={\$12,600}+{\$2,864.16}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$15,464.16}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The total equity amounts to \$15,464.16.**

To balance the total debt and equity and the total assets, we are to compute the external financing needed by the company:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{EFN}&=\text{Total Assets}-\text{Total Debt and Equity}\\[12pt]
&={\$25,356.24}-{\$24,564.16}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$792.08}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The external financing needed amounts to \$792.08.**

Now, let us prepare the final pro forma balance sheet:
&nbsp;
$$\textbf{Pro Forma}\\
\textbf{Balance Sheet}$$

$$\begin{array}{l r l r}
\text{Assets}&{\$25,356.24}&\text{Debt}&{\$9,100.00}\\
{}&{}&\text{Equity}&\underline{15,464.16}\\
\hspace{20pt}\textbf{Total }&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$}\hspace{6pt}\textbf{25,356.24}}}&\hspace{20pt}\textbf{Total }&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$}\hspace{6pt}\textbf{24,564.16}}}\\[10pt]
{}&{}&\text{EFN}&{\$\hspace{25pt}792.08}
\end{array}$$

### Followed by proving the given income statement.


$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Kerch Inc.}\\

\text{Income Statement}

\end{array}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{lr}
\textbf{Accounts}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}\\[5pt]
\text{Sales}&\$7,200.00\\
\text{Cost of Sales}&\underline{4,730.00}\\
\textbf{Net Income}&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$2,470.00}}}


\end{array}
$$

### Last, provide the given balance sheet.
$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Kerch Inc.}\\

\text{Balance Sheet}

\end{array}
$$


$$
\begin{array}{lrlr}
\textbf{Accounts}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}&\textbf{Accounts}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}\\[5pt]
\text{Assets}&\$21,700.00&\text{Liability}&\$9,100.00\\
&\underline{\text{---------}}&\text{Equity}&\underline{12,600.00}\\
\textbf{Total}&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$21,700.00}}}&\textbf{Total}&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$21,700.00}}}



\end{array}
$$

### Compute the percentage share of the cost of sales from the sales.

Computation of the percentage share of the cost of sales is needed to compute the cost of sales for the projected sales.

The formula is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Cost of Sales from Sales}&= \dfrac{\text{Cost of Sales}}{\text{Sales}}


\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the percentage of the cost of sales from sales is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Cost of Sales from Sales}&= \dfrac{\$4,730.00}{\$7,200.00}\\[15pt]
&= 0.656944444  \times 100\\[15pt]
&= \boxed{\textbf{65.69\%}}



\end{aligned}
$$

The percentage of the cost of sales from the sales is **65.69%**.

### Compute the cost of sales of the project sales.

Using the calculated percentage of the cost of sales, we will use this percentage share to calculate the projected cost of sales.

The formula is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Projected Cost of Sales} &= \text{Projected Sales} \times \text{Percentage of Cost}
\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the projected cost of sales is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Projected Cost of Sales} &= \$8,424.00 \times 65.69\%\\[15pt]
&= \boxed{\textbf{\$5,533.73}}
\end{aligned}
$$

The projected cost of sales is **$5,533.73**.

### Compute the projected net income using the Pro-forma income statement.

After computing the projected cost of sales, we can now calculate the projected net income.

The calculation is as follows.

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Kerch Inc.}\\
\text{Pro Forma}\\
\text{Income Statement}

\end{array}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{lr}
\textbf{Accounts}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}\\[5pt]
\text{Sales}&\$8,424.00\\
\text{Cost of Sales}&\underline{5,533.73}\\
\textbf{Net Income}&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$2,890.27}}}


\end{array}
$$



Therefore, the projected net income is **$2,890.27**.

### Compute the percentage of increase in sales.

The percentage of increase in sales will be used to calculate the company's projected assets.


The formula is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Increase in Sales}&= \dfrac{\text{Projected Sales}}{\text{ Current Sales}}


\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the percentage of increase in sales.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Increase in Sales}&= \dfrac{\$8,424.00}{\$7,200.00}\\[15pt]
&= 1.17  \times 100\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\textbf{117\%}}


\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore,  the percentage increase in sales is **117%** or the sales increased by **17%**.

### Compute the projected assets.

Assets are to be projected in proportion to the increase in sales. 

The formula is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Projected Assets} &= \text{Assets} \times \text{Percentage of increase in sales}
\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the projected assets are calculated as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Projected Assets} &= \$21,700 \times 117\%\\[15pt]
&= \boxed{\textbf{\$25,389.00}}
\end{aligned}
$$


Therefore, the projected assets are **$25,389.00**.

### Prepare the Pro-forma balance sheet.

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Kerch Inc.}\\
\text{Pro Forma}\\
\text{Balance Sheet}

\end{array}
$$
$$
\begin{array}{lrlr}
\textbf{Accounts}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}&\textbf{Accounts}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}\\[5pt]
\text{Assets}&\$25,389.00&\text{Liability}&\$9,100.00\\
&\underline{\text{---------}}&\text{Equity}&\underline{15,490.27}\\
\textbf{Total}&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$25,389.00}}}&\textbf{Total}&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$24,590.27}}}\\[10pt]
&&\textbf{EFN}&\underline{\$798.73}\\
&&\textbf{New Total}&\underline{\underline{\textbf{\$25,389.00}}}



\end{array}
$$

Therefore, the new total of the balance sheet is **$25,389.00**.
